# AutoAgency — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
AutoAgency is a full-stack AI SaaS dashboard for autonomous social media management. Users manage 100+ social accounts, drop in content (URL/text) and Claude AI generates short-form posts, reply angles, and long-form articles distributed across their account fleet.

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React 18 + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + ShadCN UI (dark mode)
- Backend: Express.js + TypeScript
- Database: PostgreSQL with Drizzle ORM (via @neondatabase/serverless)
- AI: Anthropic Claude Sonnet 4 (user's own API key, NOT Replit AI Integrations)
- Routing: wouter (client), Express (server)
- State Management: TanStack Query (React Query)
- Charts: Recharts
- Build: Vite (frontend), esbuild (server)

## Architecture Rules

### Data Flow
1. Schema defined in `shared/schema.ts` — single source of truth for types
2. Storage layer in `server/storage.ts` — all DB operations go through `IStorage` interface
3. Routes in `server/routes.ts` — thin handlers that validate with Zod and delegate to storage
4. API hooks in `client/src/lib/api.ts` — TanStack Query hooks for all endpoints
5. Pages in `client/src/pages/` — React components that consume hooks

### When Adding Features
1. Start with `shared/schema.ts` — define tables, insert schemas, types
2. Add CRUD methods to `IStorage` interface and `DatabaseStorage` in `server/storage.ts`
3. Add routes in `server/routes.ts` with Zod validation on all inputs
4. Add TanStack Query hooks in `client/src/lib/api.ts`
5. Create page component in `client/src/pages/`
6. Register route in `client/src/App.tsx`
7. Add nav item in `client/src/components/layout/AppLayout.tsx`
8. Run `npm run db:push` to sync schema

### Key Files to Understand
- `shared/schema.ts` — All Drizzle table definitions, Zod insert schemas, TypeScript types
- `server/storage.ts` — `IStorage` interface + `DatabaseStorage` implementation
- `server/routes.ts` — All Express API routes
- `server/ai.ts` — Claude API integration (3 functions: generateContentFromSource, generateReply, analyzeAccountPerformance)
- `client/src/lib/api.ts` — All TanStack Query hooks (useAccounts, usePosts, useAgentConfigs, etc.)
- `client/src/components/layout/AppLayout.tsx` — Sidebar navigation + header

## Code Conventions

### Backend
- All PATCH routes must validate with `.partial()` Zod schemas from drizzle-zod
- All route params must check for `isNaN(id)` and return 400
- Storage methods return `undefined` for not-found; routes return 404 JSON
- Error responses always use `{ error: "message" }` format
- AI functions in `server/ai.ts` use `process.env.ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` directly — never use Replit AI Integrations billing

### Frontend
- Use `wouter` for routing (not react-router)
- All API calls go through hooks in `client/src/lib/api.ts` — never raw fetch in components
- Use `useMutation` with `onSuccess` that invalidates related query keys
- Add `data-testid` to all interactive elements: `{action}-{target}` pattern
- Add `data-testid` to data display elements: `{type}-{content}-{id}` pattern

### Styling
- Dark mode only — background `hsl(224, 71%, 4%)`, primary `hsl(210, 100%, 50%)`
- Use `glass-card` utility class for glassmorphic card components
- Fonts: Inter (body), Plus Jakarta Sans (headings/display)
- Status indicators use colored dots with `shadow-[0_0_8px_...]` glow
- Animations: `animate-in fade-in slide-in-from-bottom-4 duration-500`

### Database
- Use Drizzle ORM exclusively — no raw SQL in application code
- Schema changes go in `shared/schema.ts`, then `npm run db:push`
- Foreign keys use `onDelete: "cascade"` for owned relations, `onDelete: "set null"` for optional refs
- Array columns use `.array()` method syntax: `text().array()` not `array(text())`

## API Endpoints Reference

### Accounts
- `GET /api/accounts` — list all
- `GET /api/accounts/stats` — health statistics
- `POST /api/accounts` — create
- `PATCH /api/accounts/:id` — update
- `DELETE /api/accounts/:id` — delete
- `POST /api/accounts/:id/analyze` — Claude AI analysis

### Content
- `GET /api/content-sources` — list all
- `POST /api/content-sources` — create
- `POST /api/content-sources/:id/generate` — generate AI content

### Posts
- `GET /api/posts` — list (optional `?contentSourceId=`)
- `GET /api/posts/top` — top by impressions (`?limit=`)
- `GET /api/posts/scheduled` — draft/scheduled/pending queue
- `PATCH /api/posts/:id` — update status/content

### Reply Operations
- `GET /api/reply-angles` — list angles
- `GET /api/reply-opportunities` — list opportunities
- `POST /api/reply-opportunities` — create
- `POST /api/reply-opportunities/:id/generate-reply` — generate AI reply
- `PATCH /api/reply-opportunities/:id` — update status

### Agents
- `GET /api/agents` — list configs
- `POST /api/agents` — create
- `PATCH /api/agents/:id` — update

### System
- `GET /api/dashboard/stats` — aggregated stats
- `GET /api/health` — health check

## Environment Variables
- `DATABASE_URL` — PostgreSQL connection string
- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` — User's Anthropic Claude API key

## Common Tasks

### "Add a new database table"
1. Define in `shared/schema.ts` with `pgTable`
2. Create `insertSchema` with `createInsertSchema().omit({ id: true, createdAt: true })`
3. Export insert type with `z.infer` and select type with `$inferSelect`
4. Add methods to `IStorage` and `DatabaseStorage`
5. Run `npm run db:push`

### "Add a new API endpoint"
1. Add route in `server/routes.ts`
2. Validate body with Zod schema from `shared/schema.ts`
3. Use `storage` methods for all DB ops
4. Return consistent JSON format

### "Add a new page"
1. Create component in `client/src/pages/`
2. Import and register in `client/src/App.tsx` Switch
3. Add nav item in `AppLayout.tsx` navItems array
4. Use hooks from `client/src/lib/api.ts` for data

### "Make Claude do something new"
1. Add function in `server/ai.ts`
2. Use `getClient()` helper (checks for API key)
3. Model: `claude-sonnet-4-20250514`
4. Parse JSON responses with fallback handling
5. Add route in `server/routes.ts` to expose it
6. Add mutation hook in `client/src/lib/api.ts`
